    "summary": "Yes — author's own gloss + TN works, withdrawing pre-critical",
    "content": "\n**Yes, this works.**\n\nIt respects the author's own choice of gloss, which carries textual authority. The TN does the precision work (\"pre-nihilist\") without burdening the main text. And \"traditional metaphysics\" / \"post-metaphysics\" is a natural pairing in English -- it reads as \"the tradition\" vs. \"what comes after the tradition,\" which is exactly the author's intent.\n\nMy concern about \"traditional metaphysics\" carrying a dismissive connotation in English analytic philosophy contexts is real but minor -- the TN mitigates it by specifying that \"traditional\" means \"before the nihilistic crisis\" rather than \"outdated.\" And the 后形而上学 essay's own argument treats traditional metaphysics with respect (it is not wrong, just structurally unaware), which will further counteract any dismissive reading.\n\nI withdraw my \"pre-critical\" recommendation. The author's own voice should prevail when it works in English, and here it does.\n"
